    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.48B/45: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woods</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 9—12:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Situation now thoroughly in hand. Five destroyers arrived from Chefoo and Admiral
                    Anderson on Flagship <hi rend="italic">Huron</hi> reached Yokohama this
                    afternoon. All American survivors Yokohama on ships and in safety. Embassy
                    evacuated 140 American tourists Tokio today on American destroyers and 21
                    British tourists.</p>
                <p>Relief ships being landed [<hi rend="italic">loaded?</hi>] in Tsingtau and
                    Manila. Arrival of fleet dispels danger of hunger among Americans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woods</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
